div.p:
Long hath mine heart burnt within me,
      Psal. 39. 3. with an earnest, Quid retribuam? In regard Psal. 116. 12. of those gratious encouragements, by your Honour conferd upon me. Nor have I slept in the Land of forgetfulnesse, but waited opportunity to vent my selfe;

 and now I have borrowed so much strength of boldnesse, as to lift up the eyes of Hope, presuming to prefer these flashes to your view; in the which as the bad-borrowers of these dayes, I doe pay my great debts by small Pensions.
